    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="975"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d975">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.0031/5–2245</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chinese Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Soong</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clayton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Francisco</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-25">May 25,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Clayton</hi>: I am in receipt of your two letters
                    of May 22, one concerning registration of American firms in China,<note n="64"
                        xml:id="d975fn64">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1216">p. 1216</ref>.</note>
                    and the <pb facs="1326" n="1316" xml:id="pg_1316"/> second concerning draft
                    treaty of friendship and commerce between China and the United States.<note
                        n="65" xml:id="d975fn65">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> I also have the enclosed copy of draft
                    treaty and copy of memorandum to the Embassy at Chungking for use in negotiating
                    treaty.</p>
                <p>These are having my careful attention and I shall look forward to discussing them
                    with you and your staff when I return to Washington on my way home.</p>
                <p>Yours sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>T. V. <hi rend="smallcaps">Soong</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
